I remember

281
00:16:33,880 --> 00:16:35,760
it was sent during Xushi that night.

282
00:16:35,760 --> 00:16:37,560
Maybe the timing doesn't match.

283
00:16:38,120 --> 00:16:39,280
What time is it now?

284
00:16:39,520 --> 00:16:40,760
It is Wushi now.

285
00:16:41,240 --> 00:16:43,240
What time was Sun Wenhuai arrested?

286
00:16:43,280 --> 00:16:44,520
Also Wushi.

287
00:16:46,000 --> 00:16:47,480
You mean

288
00:16:47,560 --> 00:16:49,760
at Wushi on this day 17 years ago,

289
00:16:49,800 --> 00:16:51,260
Sun Wenhuai was arrested?

290
00:16:51,520 --> 00:16:54,160
And you were entrusted to put the letter in the secret compartment.

291
00:16:54,160 --> 00:16:55,040
So,

292
00:16:55,200 --> 00:16:58,040
we have to wait until the time of Xu to get a reply,

293
00:16:58,160 --> 00:17:01,000
and then we'll know what's in the letter.

294
00:17:03,640 --> 00:17:05,960
It is still too early for the time of Xu.

295
00:17:06,000 --> 00:17:07,359
You might as well go back first.

296
00:17:07,359 --> 00:17:09,760
Let's go back to the yamen to check the files,

297
00:17:09,760 --> 00:17:10,720
and then see

298
00:17:10,720 --> 00:17:13,720
if there are any records of Sun Wenhuai's murder case.

299
00:17:14,079 --> 00:17:16,480
We will come back after checking the files.

300
00:17:18,920 --> 00:17:19,880
I remember

301
00:17:20,400 --> 00:17:21,800
that summer,

302
00:17:22,760 --> 00:17:24,760
the weather was exceptionally hot.

303
00:17:25,079 --> 00:17:27,680
When the new clerk was sorting out the files,

304
00:17:27,760 --> 00:17:30,420
he accidentally knocked over the candlestick.

305
00:17:30,520 --> 00:17:33,400
All the case files from April to June of that year

306
00:17:33,440 --> 00:17:35,040
were completely burned.

307
00:17:36,080 --> 00:17:37,440
The case of

308
00:17:37,840 --> 00:17:39,480
Sun Wenhuai you want to check

309
00:17:39,720 --> 00:17:42,120
happens to be burned too.

310
00:17:43,080 --> 00:17:44,600
Why such a coincidence?

311
00:17:45,400 --> 00:17:46,920
Nearly thirty

312
00:17:46,960 --> 00:17:48,760
case files were completely destroyed.

313
00:17:48,760 --> 00:17:51,680
It couldn't be helped.

314
00:17:52,240 --> 00:17:57,000
Why must you all insist on investigating such an old case?

315
00:17:58,120 --> 00:18:00,000
Since the materials no longer exist,

316
00:18:00,000 --> 00:18:03,000
there is no need for us to continue the investigation.

317
00:18:03,000 --> 00:18:05,400
We will take our leave now.

318
00:18:05,440 --> 00:18:06,600
I really couldn't help.

319
00:18:06,600 --> 00:18:08,400
I am ashamed.

320
00:18:22,440 --> 00:18:24,500
It really is a letter at the time of Xu.

321
00:18:24,840 --> 00:18:26,480
Open it and see what it says.

322
00:18:29,840 --> 00:18:30,680
This...

323
00:18:30,800 --> 00:18:32,730
Why is it a letter written in blood?

324
00:18:39,920 --> 00:18:41,920
Meeting with this sudden disaster,

325
00:18:42,480 --> 00:18:45,120
I was misunderstood by Constable Su Yu'an.

326
00:18:46,440 --> 00:18:49,280
I truly did not cause Miss Liu's death.

327
00:18:50,480 --> 00:18:52,680
The authorities have always been just.

328
00:18:53,560 --> 00:18:57,480
I believe they will get to the bottom of this case.

329
00:18:58,760 --> 00:19:00,520
If you read this letter,

330
00:19:00,960 --> 00:19:05,280
please let me know if this case has been cleared.

331
00:19:06,080 --> 00:19:08,400
I eagerly await your reply.

332
00:19:08,640 --> 00:19:12,240
How many constables in the government office are named Su Yu'an?

333
00:19:13,520 --> 00:19:14,720
I really don't know.

334
00:19:14,880 --> 00:19:17,280
He is Sun Wenhuai.

335
00:19:17,440 --> 00:19:19,640
It seems you've remembered something.

336
00:19:22,880 --> 00:19:25,000
The Miss Liu he mentioned

337
00:19:26,040 --> 00:19:27,840
should be Liu Shiqin.

338
00:19:31,680 --> 00:19:34,010
She and I were neighbors since childhood.

339
00:19:34,360 --> 00:19:36,080
Childhood friends.

340
00:19:36,760 --> 00:19:39,320
Though we live far apart now,

341
00:19:39,400 --> 00:19:41,330
our friendship remains as before,

342
00:19:41,880 --> 00:19:43,680
just like real siblings.

343
00:20:04,520 --> 00:20:06,200
When others listen to my playing,

344
00:20:06,200 --> 00:20:07,720
they are full of energy.

345
00:20:08,200 --> 00:20:09,860
When you listen to my playing,

346
00:20:09,960 --> 00:20:11,680
you get drowsy.

347
00:20:12,640 --> 00:20:14,280
No, no.

348
00:20:15,320 --> 00:20:17,040
It's just that your playing

349
00:20:17,480 --> 00:20:19,160
makes me feel so peaceful,

350
00:20:19,600 --> 00:20:21,460
and cures my insomnia perfectly.

351
00:20:25,360 --> 00:20:28,040
I was just an ordinary constable back then,

352
00:20:28,240 --> 00:20:30,240
responsible for patrolling the streets.

353
00:20:30,240 --> 00:20:30,920
Brother Su.

354
00:20:30,960 --> 00:20:33,220
That night, Liu Shiqin asked me for help.

355
00:20:33,240 --> 00:20:34,160
That man is following me.

356
00:20:34,160 --> 00:20:37,440
She said she was being followed by a man,

357
00:20:37,480 --> 00:20:40,440
and felt he had malicious intent, making her afraid.

358
00:20:40,480 --> 00:20:42,640
So I reprimanded the man privately,

359
00:20:42,680 --> 00:20:44,760
warning him not to do it again.

360
00:20:47,040 --> 00:20:49,700
That day, this man went to find Liu Shiqin again.

361
00:20:50,000 --> 00:20:51,160
Liu Shiqin.

362
00:20:51,240 --> 00:20:52,920
To avoid his harassment,

363
00:20:53,040 --> 00:20:54,720
she accidentally fell from a high place

364
00:20:54,720 --> 00:20:56,080
and broke her ribs.

365
00:20:56,880 --> 00:21:00,120
But this person insisted it was unintentional.

366
00:21:02,360 --> 00:21:03,520
Why didn't you knock?

367
00:21:03,520 --> 00:21:04,320
Alright.

368
00:21:04,920 --> 00:21:06,440
Let him hear it too.

369
00:21:07,600 --> 00:21:09,240
But based on my deduction,

370
00:21:09,280 --> 00:21:12,360
he intentionally harassed Liu Shiqin.

371
00:21:12,400 --> 00:21:14,040
So I informed the magistrate

372
00:21:14,280 --> 00:21:15,920
that he did it on purpose.

373
00:21:16,240 --> 00:21:18,700
The case then entered the liability period.

374
00:21:19,840 --> 00:21:22,240
The so-called liability period means that

375
00:21:22,880 --> 00:21:27,440
if the victim's injuries worsen within a certain time

376
00:21:27,640 --> 00:21:28,920
or even lead to death,

377
00:21:29,280 --> 00:21:30,800
the perpetrator will bear

378
00:21:31,000 --> 00:21:33,160
all the criminal penalties.

379
00:21:34,280 --> 00:21:36,720
Since Liu Shiqin broke her ribs,

380
00:21:37,160 --> 00:21:40,040
the liability period is 50 days.

381
00:21:44,080 --> 00:21:46,000
On the twentieth day, Shiqin,

382
00:21:46,000 --> 00:21:48,640
Liu Shiqin succumbed to her injuries

383
00:21:49,040 --> 00:21:51,560
and died in her bed at home.

384
00:21:51,640 --> 00:21:52,400
Shiqin!

385
00:21:52,440 --> 00:21:54,280
Since it was within the probationary period,

386
00:21:54,280 --> 00:21:55,040
How could this happen?

387
00:21:55,040 --> 00:21:58,320
the man was convicted of murder.

388
00:21:58,760 --> 00:22:00,920
I only remember that man's face,

389
00:22:01,200 --> 00:22:02,880
but I don't know his name.

390
00:22:02,920 --> 00:22:06,200
I didn't know he had a brother named Sun Wuwei.

391
00:22:06,560 --> 00:22:08,920
So you are the one who framed my brother.

392
00:22:09,320 --> 00:22:11,840
He didn't mean to break Liu Shiqin's ribs,

393
00:22:11,960 --> 00:22:13,960
but you insisted it was deliberate.

394
00:22:14,120 --> 00:22:15,240
My brother's death

395
00:22:15,280 --> 00:22:16,940
has everything to do with you.

396
00:22:16,960 --> 00:22:18,020
What are you doing?

397
00:22:18,040 --> 00:22:18,800
Don't move.

398
00:22:19,480 --> 00:22:20,040
Let me go!

399
00:22:20,040 --> 00:22:20,700
Don't move!

400
00:22:20,840 --> 00:22:21,680
Su Lang!

401
00:22:22,840 --> 00:22:23,680
Let him go.

402
00:22:31,360 --> 00:22:32,360
Sun Wuwei.

403
00:22:33,160 --> 00:22:36,240
A fight won't bring your brother back,

404
00:22:36,480 --> 00:22:38,360
nor will it help us find the truth.

405
00:22:39,200 --> 00:22:42,080
If we were in Constable Su's shoes at the time,

406
00:22:42,120 --> 00:22:44,120
he did nothing wrong.

407
00:22:48,040 --> 00:22:50,520
If your older brother was truly wronged,

408
00:22:51,440 --> 00:22:52,680
we should sit down,

409
00:22:53,200 --> 00:22:54,440
calm down,

410
00:22:54,480 --> 00:22:55,540
unravel the clues,

411
00:22:55,560 --> 00:22:57,090
and investigate the cause.

412
00:22:58,440 --> 00:22:59,240
Constable Su.

413
00:23:00,200 --> 00:23:02,720
Who did Liu Shiqin's autopsy back then?

414
00:23:02,760 --> 00:23:04,690
Were there any suspicious points?

415
00:23:06,080 --> 00:23:10,240
I later brought Liu Shiqin's body back to the yamen.

416
00:23:10,600 --> 00:23:13,720
It was personally examined by the coroner Qin Boyan.

417
00:23:14,280 --> 00:23:16,840
The coroner's report was very clear.

418
00:23:16,880 --> 00:23:19,600
She fell from a height 20 days ago,

419
00:23:19,680 --> 00:23:21,040
which broke two ribs.

420
00:23:21,080 --> 00:23:23,920
Her liver ruptured and she bled to death.

421
00:23:24,280 --> 00:23:26,440
There were no new injuries in the past 20 days.

422
00:23:26,440 --> 00:23:28,160
So the cause of her death

423
00:23:28,200 --> 00:23:31,360
was just the injury from 20 days ago.

424
00:23:31,720 --> 00:23:33,850
Then what about the coroner's report?

425
00:23:34,160 --> 00:23:35,120
Did you forget?

426
00:23:35,560 --> 00:23:37,240
Today we went to the archives.

427
00:23:37,240 --> 00:23:38,400
Registrar Fang said

428
00:23:38,480 --> 00:23:40,560
the fire had burned the files.

429
00:23:41,840 --> 00:23:44,040
That's the most suspicious part.

430
00:23:44,440 --> 00:23:48,000
Why were only the files from April to June of that year burned?

431
00:23:48,760 --> 00:23:51,440
I know you find it suspicious,

432
00:23:51,480 --> 00:23:54,410
but there's no way for us to continue investigating.

433
00:23:54,520 --> 00:23:56,640
This case is very old,

434
00:23:56,800 --> 00:23:58,360
and both the suspect and the victim

435
00:23:58,360 --> 00:23:59,820
have already passed away.

436
00:23:59,960 --> 00:24:01,400
The files are gone too.

437
00:24:01,520 --> 00:24:02,760
Unless

438
00:24:03,400 --> 00:24:05,840
we can question Sun Wenhuai from back then.

439
00:24:08,160 --> 00:24:10,040
I put the letter from my brother into the secret compartment.

440
00:24:10,040 --> 00:24:11,040
Since there was no response,

441
00:24:11,040 --> 00:24:12,370
I never opened it again.

442
00:24:12,880 --> 00:24:14,600
To pay for my brother's lawsuit,

443
00:24:14,600 --> 00:24:15,960
I sold all the furniture in the house

444
00:24:15,960 --> 00:24:17,560
to the secondhand shop.

445
00:24:17,960 --> 00:24:20,220
But in the end, we still lost the lawsuit.

446
00:24:20,400 --> 00:24:22,000
Filled with grief and indignation, I made a scene at the government office.

447
00:24:22,000 --> 00:24:23,440
I was exiled to Lingnan,

448
00:24:23,480 --> 00:24:25,440
and only returned to Luoyang half a year ago.

449
00:24:25,440 --> 00:24:26,440
Now,

450
00:24:27,120 --> 00:24:29,580
I make a living by making sesame flatbreads.

451
00:24:29,600 --> 00:24:32,920
So even if we write a letter to ask about the case,

452
00:24:32,960 --> 00:24:35,320
you from 17 years ago wouldn't be able to read it.

453
00:24:35,320 --> 00:24:36,850
Wouldn't be able to read it.

454
00:24:37,400 --> 00:24:39,560
Do we have any other options?

455
00:24:39,920 --> 00:24:42,840
If Qin Boyan was really the one who did the autopsy back then,

456
00:24:42,840 --> 00:24:45,120
he must have kept a draft.

457
00:24:49,720 --> 00:24:52,080
When I bought the Corpse Observation Record in the ghost market,

458
00:24:52,080 --> 00:24:53,680
the broker there told me

459
00:24:53,760 --> 00:24:56,080
that Qin Boyan had a habit when doing autopsies.

460
00:24:56,080 --> 00:24:57,400
After every autopsy,

461
00:24:57,440 --> 00:24:59,040
he would keep a draft.

462
00:24:59,240 --> 00:25:02,200
Because he well knew the hardships of coroners,

463
00:25:02,360 --> 00:25:06,000
and also to make it convenient for people to learn and reference.

464
00:25:06,920 --> 00:25:08,840
After the fire at the Qin family,

465
00:25:09,120 --> 00:25:11,120
a lot of things were indeed lost.

466
00:25:11,760 --> 00:25:14,560
Did those things end up in the ghost market?

467
00:25:14,840 --> 00:25:18,280
Valuable things naturally have their own ways of circulating.

468
00:25:18,280 --> 00:25:20,520
You actually have such a treasure?

469
00:25:27,680 --> 00:25:29,400
The deceased Liu Shiqin.

470
00:25:29,520 --> 00:25:32,040
The ribs on the lower left of her chest were broken.

471
00:25:32,040 --> 00:25:33,640
The broken ends pierced her liver,

472
00:25:33,640 --> 00:25:35,160
causing unstoppable bleeding,

473
00:25:35,160 --> 00:25:37,160
leading to severe injury and death.

474
00:25:37,280 --> 00:25:39,440
The marks of the broken bone do not look like an old injury.

475
00:25:39,440 --> 00:25:41,840
It seems someone inflicted further harm on the old injury.

476
00:25:41,840 --> 00:25:43,480
Therefore, the cause of death is suspicious.

477
00:25:43,480 --> 00:25:46,560
It is not solely due to the fall from the stairs 20 days ago.

478
00:25:46,560 --> 00:25:48,320
There might be a hidden truth.

479
00:25:51,120 --> 00:25:53,160
Then this autopsy report is enough to prove

480
00:25:53,160 --> 00:25:57,020
that my brother is not the real culprit who caused Liu Shiqin's death.

481
00:25:57,080 --> 00:25:58,800
Is the information in this autopsy report true, Constable Su?

482
00:25:58,800 --> 00:26:00,760
The autopsy report states it clearly.

483
00:26:00,760 --> 00:26:02,490
Why is what you said different?

484
00:26:02,520 --> 00:26:04,280
Or are you lying?

485
00:26:08,280 --> 00:26:09,440
This is not right.

486
00:26:11,840 --> 00:26:13,120
I didn't lie.

487
00:26:13,360 --> 00:26:15,760
It was written clearly on the autopsy report back then.

488
00:26:15,760 --> 00:26:16,440
Otherwise,

489
00:26:16,480 --> 00:26:20,000
the government office wouldn't have sentenced Sun Wenhuai to death for murder.

490
00:26:20,000 --> 00:26:22,800
Do you think the whole government office would lie along with me?

491
00:26:22,800 --> 00:26:23,760
Right.

492
00:26:24,400 --> 00:26:26,720
How can we prove that this is definitely Qin Boyan's handwriting?

493
00:26:26,720 --> 00:26:28,200
It could also be forged.

494
00:26:28,560 --> 00:26:31,080
Qin Boyan did so many autopsies for the government office.

495
00:26:31,080 --> 00:26:33,000
As long as we find the autopsy reports in the files

496
00:26:33,000 --> 00:26:34,200
and compare them,

497
00:26:34,240 --> 00:26:35,840
the truth will be clear at a glance.

498
00:26:35,840 --> 00:26:37,000
And I believe

499
00:26:37,280 --> 00:26:40,200
the one in the master advisor's hand must be fake,

500
00:26:40,240 --> 00:26:41,680
so it couldn't be kept.

501
00:26:41,840 --> 00:26:43,240
This perfectly explains

502
00:26:43,440 --> 00:26:44,480
why the files that were burned

503
00:26:44,480 --> 00:26:47,240
happened to be from April to June of that year.

504
00:26:48,160 --> 00:26:50,640
That means this master advisor was forging it.

505
00:26:50,640 --> 00:26:51,160
He has a problem.

506
00:26:51,160 --> 00:26:52,640
Arrest him.

507
00:26:52,680 --> 00:26:55,760
The master advisor died many years ago.

508
00:26:56,800 --> 00:26:57,960
How did he die?

509
00:26:59,720 --> 00:27:01,600
He died of a stroke at home.

510
00:27:02,000 --> 00:27:03,860
It seems the lead is broken again.

511
00:27:06,000 --> 00:27:09,440
If Liu Shiqin was murdered while recovering from her injuries,

512
00:27:09,440 --> 00:27:11,160
and the autopsy report was forged

513
00:27:11,160 --> 00:27:14,160
to frame Sun Wenhuai, who was in his probation period,

514
00:27:16,080 --> 00:27:17,640
then we just need to figure out

515
00:27:17,640 --> 00:27:20,760
who benefits most from her death.

516
00:27:21,720 --> 00:27:22,960
That's right.

517
00:27:24,840 --> 00:27:26,640
After Liu Shiqin's death,

518
00:27:27,000 --> 00:27:28,860
her father became seriously ill.

519
00:27:29,000 --> 00:27:32,160
He passed away in less than a year.

520
00:27:32,920 --> 00:27:34,800
All of her father's property

521
00:27:35,080 --> 00:27:37,610
was passed to his adopted daughter, Liu Qing.

522
00:27:37,760 --> 00:27:39,640
And Liu Qing's husband, Chen You,

523
00:27:41,440 --> 00:27:43,370
is the current county magistrate.

524
00:27:43,480 --> 00:27:45,040
To find out the truth,

525
00:27:45,520 --> 00:27:47,520
we need to visit Baicao Pharmacy again.

526
00:27:47,520 --> 00:27:49,720
That wicked woman is finally in prison.

527
00:27:50,040 --> 00:27:52,360
I never expected her to harm Wang Wan.

528
00:27:53,680 --> 00:27:56,440
Now, I'll just pretend I never married her.

529
00:27:57,200 --> 00:27:59,520
However, Wang Wan has moved back in.

530
00:28:00,600 --> 00:28:01,400
My daughter.

531
00:28:02,360 --> 00:28:05,040
In the past, because of that wicked woman,

532
00:28:05,320 --> 00:28:08,040
I rarely communicated with my daughter.

533
00:28:08,440 --> 00:28:10,240
Now that we spend more time together,

534
00:28:10,240 --> 00:28:11,360
I realize

535
00:28:11,960 --> 00:28:14,480
how sensible she is.

536
00:28:17,920 --> 00:28:18,880
Dr. Wang.

537
00:28:19,600 --> 00:28:21,330
The world is full of hardships.

538
00:28:21,680 --> 00:28:23,400
Family ties are unbreakable.

539
00:28:23,920 --> 00:28:25,280
It is truly a blessing.

540
00:28:26,120 --> 00:28:27,360
I came today

541
00:28:27,600 --> 00:28:29,160
to ask you about something.

542
00:28:29,560 --> 00:28:32,160
It's about Liu Shiqin's father, Liu Jingzhao.

543
00:28:32,240 --> 00:28:33,200
As far as I know,

544
00:28:33,400 --> 00:28:35,840
Liu Jingzhao often came here for medicine before he died.

545
00:28:35,840 --> 00:28:37,000
Is this true?

546
00:28:37,200 --> 00:28:38,560
Yes, it is true.

547
00:28:39,440 --> 00:28:40,840
What disease did he have?

548
00:28:40,920 --> 00:28:41,920
Diabetes.

549
00:28:42,360 --> 00:28:44,040
When he came to me for medicine,

550
00:28:44,040 --> 00:28:45,720
he was already terminally ill. The medicine is ready.

551
00:28:45,720 --> 00:28:47,960
Taking medicine was just to maintain his condition. Thank you.

552
00:28:47,960 --> 00:28:48,720
At that time,

553
00:28:48,760 --> 00:28:52,480
I prescribed him snakegourd root, dwarf lilyturf, and Rehmannia.

554
00:28:52,480 --> 00:28:55,640
These herbs can relieve the discomfort to some extent,

555
00:28:55,840 --> 00:28:57,840
but they cannot cure it completely.

556
00:28:58,400 --> 00:29:01,200
Do you remember when he came for the consultation?

557
00:29:01,960 --> 00:29:03,560
It's been a long time.

558
00:29:03,880 --> 00:29:05,360
I can't quite remember.

559
00:29:06,200 --> 00:29:09,360
Was Liu Shiqin still alive at that time?

560
00:29:09,640 --> 00:29:11,520
When Liu Shiqin was recovering at home,

561
00:29:11,520 --> 00:29:12,650
he was already blind

562
00:29:12,680 --> 00:29:14,410
and had lost his sense of taste.

563
00:29:14,960 --> 00:29:15,960
Why is that?

564
00:29:16,400 --> 00:29:19,360
This is because when the wasting-thirst disease becomes severe,

565
00:29:19,360 --> 00:29:22,240
the toxins in the body erode the meridians.

566
00:29:23,760 --> 00:29:25,120
That means

567
00:29:25,480 --> 00:29:27,560
while Liu Shiqin was recovering,

568
00:29:27,680 --> 00:29:29,560
her father was already terminally ill.

569
00:29:29,560 --> 00:29:30,280
Exactly.

570
00:29:33,240 --> 00:29:34,720
Enjoy your tea, everyone.

571
00:29:34,840 --> 00:29:36,240
I need to get back to work.

572
00:29:36,280 --> 00:29:36,760
Okay, thank you.

573
00:29:36,760 --> 00:29:37,480
Please.

574
00:29:38,520 --> 00:29:39,360
Let's go.

575
00:29:42,120 --> 00:29:42,920
Constable Su.

576
00:29:43,680 --> 00:29:45,200
Liu Shiqin and Liu Qing,

577
00:29:45,360 --> 00:29:46,890
how is their relationship?

578
00:29:50,680 --> 00:29:53,540
They are not as close as normal biological sisters.

579
00:29:53,800 --> 00:29:57,280
But since they live under the same roof after all,

580
00:29:57,760 --> 00:29:59,040
they get along fine.

581
00:29:59,760 --> 00:30:02,400
Where was Liu Qing before she was adopted?

582
00:30:03,800 --> 00:30:06,120
I think it was Jingkong Temple.

583
00:30:07,160 --> 00:30:09,800
Then why did he adopt Liu Qing?

584
00:30:11,880 --> 00:30:15,040
Well, I'm not too sure about that.

585
00:30:16,920 --> 00:30:19,480
Did Mr. Liu leave a will?

586
00:30:24,080 --> 00:30:25,360
I think so.

587
00:30:25,720 --> 00:30:26,600
I see.

588
00:30:27,160 --> 00:30:27,640
Su Lang.

589
00:30:28,160 --> 00:30:30,280
Hurry up and investigate if this happened.

590
00:30:30,280 --> 00:30:32,240
After the investigation, let's go to the government office.

591
00:30:32,240 --> 00:30:34,840
No, let's meet back at the mansion.

592
00:30:35,040 --> 00:30:35,800
Okay.

593
00:30:43,960 --> 00:30:45,680
Such an old case,

594
00:30:45,880 --> 00:30:47,880
why are they reinvestigating it?

595
00:30:48,320 --> 00:30:49,760
It doesn't make sense.

596
00:30:51,080 --> 00:30:52,000
Moreover,

597
00:30:52,400 --> 00:30:56,360
there's nothing related to this case happening now.

598
00:30:56,560 --> 00:30:58,480
I heard the last man say

599
00:30:58,520 --> 00:31:00,840
he's going to Jingkong Temple.

600
00:31:06,080 --> 00:31:08,560
The Buliangren they just met,

601
00:31:08,720 --> 00:31:10,640
where does Jueming live?

602
00:31:18,240 --> 00:31:19,960
Go, go, go.

603
00:31:37,120 --> 00:31:39,600
Is Sun Wenhuai not dead?

604
00:31:40,080 --> 00:31:41,200
Impossible.

605
00:31:41,320 --> 00:31:43,360
He clearly died.

606
00:31:44,560 --> 00:31:46,280
Guo Cheng, come here.

607
00:31:46,440 --> 00:31:47,160
Come here.

608
00:31:50,200 --> 00:31:51,080
Look.

609
00:31:53,560 --> 00:31:54,680
Prefect Chen.

610
00:31:54,960 --> 00:31:56,720
Sun Wenhuai was beheaded.

611
00:31:56,840 --> 00:31:58,640
We were all watching at the execution ground.

612
00:31:58,640 --> 00:32:00,200
It's impossible he's not dead.

613
00:32:00,200 --> 00:32:01,360
According to what they said,

614
00:32:01,360 --> 00:32:02,720
it was through this table

615
00:32:02,720 --> 00:32:04,920
that they made contact with each other.

616
00:32:06,280 --> 00:32:07,480
You mean

617
00:32:07,920 --> 00:32:11,120
this table connects the past and the present

618
00:32:11,200 --> 00:32:12,400
and intertwines them?

619
00:32:12,400 --> 00:32:13,840
Better to believe it

620
00:32:14,480 --> 00:32:16,000
than not.

621
00:32:27,040 --> 00:32:29,360
Then I'll burn this table.

622
00:32:30,360 --> 00:32:32,690
Let's see how you contact each other then.

623
00:32:47,840 --> 00:32:49,080
Sun Wenhuai,

624
00:32:49,840 --> 00:32:51,640
you don't give me peace even in death.

